entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i would love to hear about one of your trips

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i traveled for eight months in central america and i visited a lot of different countries i i went scuba diving

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: wow what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think i think intolerance injustice in the world those are probably the things that get me the most fired up

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do when you are annoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: vent to my boyfriend does that count

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yes how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am pretty good it takes it takes a lot to really get me fired up to the point where i i kinda blow my top the very few people that have seen me angry to the point where i am kind of yelling and screaming angry i do not know i just do not get there i think that i am a little bit afraid of losing my temper so i keep it under control

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was yesterday actually i argued with my boyfriend about getting getting a job i was talking about taking a job somewhere and he was being very supportive and i really wanted him to to say no do not go take that job for six months cause i would miss you and he was just being supportive so we kind of argued about that and it was ridiculous so we i ended up laughing and that was the end of the fight

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: aww that is good what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: meditate excercise go out in nature just unplug get myself away from the computer away from technology away from people

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is so good to hear

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever served in the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was probably about fifteen at the time so i think eight was is that seventeen years ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: you were very young were not you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have not for about three years i stopped because it felt like i was checking in with a parole officer i just was not enjoying the relationship i had but i still have the psychiatrist that i go to for med checks

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sucks

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you feel like therapy is useful

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do think it is useful if you have the right therapist i think if you do not have a good relationship with your therapist it can be incredibly harmful i have talked to people that have had bad experiences and and will not ever go back

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: lately i have been a little bit down i should say a little bit more down than usual because i graduated and my routine of go to school and do school things twenty four seven has come to an end and without the routine it is been a little bit weird finding out what to do with my finding a way to be productive and knowing what to do with my time it is also been a little bit depressing finding out that my intelligence and good grades in school does not translate to real world skills and there are not that many jobs for marine biologists in california

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah that sounds really hard how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: almost impossible ever since i was a little kid i had a i had trouble falling asleep and about four years ago it it became really really bad where i just could not sleep through the night i was getting about four hours of sleep sometimes i would wake up every hour and i would wake up in the morning just a complete wreck so for about four years i have been taking trazadone so i can sleep

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: have you ever seen fight club you are a virtual han so you probably have not seen that but it is it is pretty much like that i i am just a complete panicked anxious wreck i i lose my ability to deal with i lose my ability to deal with things i am much more likely to lose my temper i can not regulate my moods i am just really volatile

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see when was the last time that happened

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: probably a few months ago i think that i may have been on a trip gone away for a weekend and forgotten to take my medicine with me or something like that and then i can not sleep and so that is what happens

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay when was the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: really happy i mean i do not know it is easy for me easier for me to keep track of when i feel really really bad really happy i guess i felt happy on new year is really happy on new year is eve which was ten days ago i was with my boyfriend and some friends and we took a trip out to palm spring and joshua tree and it was really nice to see them i do not get to see them very often because i have been in school and i have been so busy so it was really nice reintroduction to real life

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great what would you say are some of your best qualities

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think that i am i am kind i am considerate i am tolerant i am pretty open minded i am aware of my faults i just i just try to be nice to everybody and i am very curious about about the world and things that i do not know about i really like to learn
